Description.description: A request to supply a diet, formula feeding (eternal) or oral nutritional supplement to a patient/resident.

Sequence number of the import that created this record.
Unique identifier of the user who modified the record.

Unique identifier of the delegate user who modified the record.
The product or brand name of the type of modular component to be added to the formula.
Indicates the type of modular component such as protein, carbohydrate, fat or fiber to be provided in addition to or mixed with the base formula.
Free text formula administration, feeding instructions or additional instructions or information.
The product or brand name of the eternal or infant formula product such as "ACME Adult Standard Formula".
The type of eternal or infant formula such as an adult standard formula with fiber or a soy-based infant formula.
The amount of energy (calories) that the formula should provide per specified volume, typically per mL or fluid oz.
The date and time that this nutrition order was requested.
An encounter that provides additional information about the healthcare context in which this request is made.
The maximum total quantity of formula that may be administered to a subject over the period of time, e.g. 1440 mL over 24 hours.

The person (patient) who needs the nutrition order for an oral diet, nutritional supplement and/or eternal or formula feeding.
The route or physiological path of administration into the patient's gastrointestinal tract for purposes of providing the formula feeding, e.g. nasogastric tube.
The workflow status of the nutrition order/request.
